# Plan standards + documentation context (required for feature plans)

Plans that only cite code paths are hard for humans to review and for non-frontier executors to align with governance. Feature plans in Umbraculum-family repos MUST open with **Standards & governance context** (first content section after YAML frontmatter), then **Documentation context**, then **Local verification before push**.

The standards block is the implementation contract: executors treat cited RFC § and coding-standard sections as binding unless the operator explicitly approves a deviation in the plan or in chat.

## When this rule fires

### Plan authoring

- Authoring or materially extending a **multi-phase** `.plan.md` or equivalent execution plan (new wave, new RFC consumer, cross-module feature).
- Handing a plan to a **non-frontier executor** — also read rule `43-non-frontier-executor-fitness-tracker.mdc` §10.
- **Finalizing a plan for handoff** — YAML `todos` MUST include applicable rows from **Local verification before push** (section 3 below) as explicit, checkable todo items.

Does **not** fire for one-line fixes, typo-only docs, or plans explicitly marked documentation-only with `apparatus: override`.

### Implementation (independent of plan authoring)

This rule also binds **executors and agents implementing code** (with or without a written plan):

- After non-doc changes, run **pertinent** verification for the change surface — **not** every GHA workflow.
- Use section 3 matrix + consuming repo `docs/VERIFICATION-TIERS.md` + node-react rules `76-verification-tiers-gate`, `72-ci-parity-local-vs-ci-divergence`, `75-api-integration-pre-push-gate`.
- **Before declaring done:** T0 or T1 (named slice / `--from-diff`).
- **Before push:** T2 for the same pertinent jobs (ci-parity subset + API integration when `services/api/**` or path-filtered packages changed).

Local full `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity` can exceed GHA wall time on the **first** run until Docker named volumes warm (`docker.volumes` in `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json`; see umbraculum-dev `docs/DEVELOPMENT-NPM-VOLUMES.md`). Prefer **T1 slices during iteration**; reserve full T2 for pre-push.

## Required placement

1. YAML frontmatter (`name`, `overview`, `todos`, …) when present.
2. **`## Standards & governance context (required)`** — MUST be the first markdown heading after frontmatter.
3. **`## Documentation context (required)`** — immediately after the standards block.
4. **`## Local verification before push (required)`** — immediately after documentation context.
5. Plan body (phases, executor steps, todos).

Do not bury RFC or coding-standard citations only in phase prose. If a standard applies to the whole plan, cite it in section 2 above.

Do not hand off a plan whose frontmatter `todos` omit section 3 verification items for the plan's change surface.

## Required section 1 — Standards & governance context

```markdown
## Standards & governance context (required)

**Binding for implementation:** phases below MUST follow these unless the operator explicitly approves a deviation.

| Role | Document |
|------|----------|
| Governing RFC | [RFC-0007](docs/rfcs/0007-....md) — §N (list bullets the plan implements) |
| Coding standards | [CODING-STANDARDS.md](docs/CODING-STANDARDS.md) — § headings that apply |
| Foundation gates | [LINTING.md](docs/LINTING.md), [TESTING.md](docs/TESTING.md), [TYPING.md](docs/TYPING.md) — when TS/JS code changes |
| Cross-platform | [CROSS-PLATFORM-BOUNDARIES.md](docs/CROSS-PLATFORM-BOUNDARIES.md) — when touching `apps/web`, `apps/native`, or shared packages |
| Plugin rules | `22-typescript-contracts-runtime-validation.mdc`, `45-public-endpoint-verification.mdc`, … |
| Runbook | [DEVELOPMENT.md](DEVELOPMENT.md) — container npm, CI parity, rendering stack |

**Applicable coding-standard sections (explicit):**
- [ ] Native-ready packages / `dist/` discipline
- [ ] Shared logic over copying / package placement
- [ ] External API runtime validation (`unknown` → parse)
- [ ] `@umbraculum/contracts` versioning
- [ ] UI layering (`@umbraculum/ui` vs domain packages vs app adapters)
- [ ] _(add or strike rows — unchecked rows MUST NOT apply to this plan)_
```

Rules for section 1:

- Use **repo-relative markdown links**.
- **Governing RFC** — cite § numbers and name the RFC bullets the plan implements (not just the RFC title).
- **Coding standards** — umbraculum-dev canonical path: `docs/CODING-STANDARDS.md`. Sister repos: equivalent path or strike the row with `(n/a — <repo> has no coding-standards doc)`.
- **Foundation gates** — include when the plan touches TS/JS; strike or omit for docs-only or non-TS repos.
- **Plugin rules** — cite by **filename** (witness contract in consuming repo's `docs/CURSOR-PLUGINS.md`).
- **Applicable coding-standard sections** — checklist MUST reflect this plan; do not leave all boxes checked by default.

## Required section 2 — Documentation context

```markdown
## Documentation context (required)

| Role | Document |
|------|----------|
| Horizontal surface | [canonical-....md](docs/design/....md) |
| Module surface | [canonical-....md](docs/design/....md) §N |
| Build log pattern | [....-build-log.md](docs/design/....md) |
| Non-frontier traps | [NON-FRONTIER-EXECUTOR-FITNESS-TRACKER.md](docs/NON-FRONTIER-EXECUTOR-FITNESS-TRACKER.md) §10 |
```

Governing RFC and coding standards live in section 1 — do not duplicate them here unless a companion surface doc also needs a § cite.

Template: `docs/design/plan-documentation-context-template.md` in umbraculum-dev (or equivalent in sibling repos).

## Required section 3 — Local verification before push (required)

List **only** workflows that apply to this plan's change surface. Strike rows that do not apply.

```markdown
## Local verification before push (required)

**Executor rule:** run pertinent rows before push — not every GHA workflow. During implementation use T0/T1; before push use T2 equivalents.

| Change surface (this plan) | Before done (T0/T1) | Before push (T2) | GHA workflow(s) |
|----------------------------|---------------------|------------------|-----------------|
| Docs / README only | — | `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity run --jobs docs-readmes` | `docs-readmes.yml` |
| TS/JS lint surface | `npm run verify:from-diff` or named slice | `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity run --jobs lint` | `web-lint.yml` |
| TS typecheck surface | scoped slice + `build-package-in-docker.sh` as needed | `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity run --jobs typecheck` | `typecheck.yml` |
| `services/api/**`, OpenAPI, contracts routes | `npm run verify:openapi` | ci-parity pertinent jobs **+** skill `api-integration-tests-pre-push` | `api.yml` + ci-parity |
| `packages/**` dist / SDK | `check-packages-dist-up-to-date.sh` | `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity run --jobs sdk-publish-prep` (when SDK batch) | `packages-dist-check.yml`, `publish-sdk-batch.yml` |
| Full unknown mixed diff | `npm run verify:from-diff` | `npm run verify:pre-push` | all ci-parity + API reminder |

**Skills (node-react plugin):** `verify-slice-runbook`, `scoped-package-build-in-docker`, `ci-parity-local-reproduction`, `api-integration-tests-pre-push`, `docker-npm-volumes-runbook`.

**Plan YAML todos (required at plan completion):** for each **non-struck** row above, add one frontmatter todo (YAML frontmatter `todos:` list with ids like `verify-t1-openapi`, `verify-t2-ci-parity`, `verify-t2-api` and content strings naming the T1/T2 command).

Executor phases MUST NOT mark the plan complete until these todos are checked off or explicitly waived by the operator.
```

Rules for section 3:

- **Pertinent only** — if the plan touches only `packages/contracts`, do not require `api-integration-tests-pre-push`.
- **Docs-only plans** — ci-parity `docs-readmes` job only; strike lint/typecheck/api rows.
- **Do not** list "run all GHA workflows" as a single todo — enumerate jobs from `.umbraculum/ci-parity.json` and API skill separately.
- Cross-platform entry: `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity` (not host `npm run lint`).

## Executor instructions

- Each phase MUST start with: `Follows: Standards & governance context above.`
- Enumerate **per-file artifacts** by absolute path where the plan will be executed by a subagent (platform plugin rule `97-plans-must-include-canonical-absolute-paths.mdc`).
- If the plan adds document templates, state that **horizontal rendering surface §2** must be updated in the same wave.

## Anti-patterns

- Plan opens with `## Overview` or phase 1 before standards context.
- Coding standards mentioned only in passing ("follow existing conventions") with no `CODING-STANDARDS.md` link or § checklist.
- RFC cited in frontmatter `overview` but not in section 1 with § numbers.
- Executor phases that contradict an checked coding-standard row without a documented operator-approved deviation.
- Plan handoff **without** section 3 verification todos in YAML frontmatter.
- Declaring implementation complete or pushing without running **pertinent** verification rows (running every workflow "just in case").
- Using full `npx @umbraculum/ci-parity` on every save during iteration instead of T1 slices (then blaming local slowness on CI parity itself).

## Companion skill

Use `plan-documentation-context` skill to scaffold all three required header sections from module code / RFC keywords.

## Fits the system

- **Frontier now**: always-applied plan-authoring gate; standards block at the top makes RFC + coding-standard compliance reviewable before execution starts. Section 3 + YAML todos make pre-push workflow proof explicit; executor obligation applies even without a plan.
- **Local subagents (future)**: a readonly `plan-preflight` subagent can regex-check for all three headings, a non-empty RFC row, and at least one verification todo before an executor subagent runs.
